# peer
## 1.1: Look searchingly.

  *  We peered into the back of the shop to see if a salesman was around.
  *  Peer into his eyes and you'll know what I mean.
  *  Human beings always want to peer into the nooks of the universe.

## 1.2: PEER REVIEW: evaluate professionally a colleague's work.

  *  We peer review every article in the journal.
  *  She has to peer review some work over the weekend.
